.TH "set_trigger_filter" 9 "set_trigger_filter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
set_trigger_filter \- Generic event_command @set_filter implementation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" set_trigger_filter
.BI "(char *filter_str "  ","
.BI "struct event_trigger_data *trigger_data "  ","
.BI "struct trace_event_file *file "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filter_str" 12
The filter string for the trigger, NULL to remove filter
.IP "trigger_data" 12
Trigger-specific data
.IP "file" 12
The trace_event_file associated with the event
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Common implementation for event command filter parsing and filter
instantiation.

Usually used directly as the \fIset_filter\fP method in event command
implementations.

Also used to remove a filter (if filter_str = NULL).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, errno otherwise
